# Ago, 2025 November 6th

Create a new environment

conda create -n sparvio

Install some relevant packages

conda install -c conda-forge -n sparvio pyserial jupyter cartopy pandas scipy numpy

conda install -c conda-forge -n sparvio aiohttp-jinja2

conda activate sparvio

Then I follow the install_linux.pdf

sudo apt-get install -y python-setuptools
sudo adduser <user> dialout
sudo apt remove modemmanager

python setup.py install

But this last line does not work because there is no setup.py script

If I connect the SA1 to the data logger I can do

./read_log.py --ports

to get

/dev/ttyACM0

But then if I try

sudo ./read_log.py --retain --port /dev/ttyACM0:115200bps

I get this message

